race.comment: A good contest. SABEERIA (13) jumped out well and looked one run short when heavily bet at Kilmore on debut. Has been placed in a Caulfield Heath jumpout since and will position forward from the inside gate. Brown sticks aboard and that's a strong push for her chances. NIELSEN PARK (16) is Sydney-trained and was cruelled by a wide gate at Kembla Grange 19 days ago. Caught the eye late and maps ideally today with Bates engaged. The well-bred galloper will be fitter and rates to be right in it. TROJAN KING (3) has been freshened and kept up to the mark with a jumpout. Will have taken fitness and learning and maps well. No surprise if he improves into the finish. SHOT OF SATIN (9) was lipped out at Ballarat second-up, and that reads well enough. She races forward with Meech aboard, and she will give her every chance.
